  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1939-1943</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The picture shows the construction of the ‘Tomorri’ cinema in Tirana in approximately 1940. The plate under the roof on the right displays the name, ‘Cinema FFAA Costruzione Palini’. Two construction workers are on the roof; two in front of the building. Three men wearing coats and hats are standing nearby.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The inserted name ‘Luce’ (an Italian film and photo production company) indicates that the photograph was taken during the Italian occupation of Albania between 1939 and 1943. The men’s clothing indicates that it is winter.</ab>
